 to change things in your school? To what extent did you have any experience of leadership roles in other social frameworks? How would you define the experience you accumulated? (1=hardly any experience–5= rich experience).\n2. Recruit the participants and apply the survey.\n3. Construct the variables from responses to four questionnaires (attachment anxiety and avoidance from the 13 attachment style items, and get secure attachment from low scores on both anxiety and avoidance; trait anxiety score (reversing relevant items first – there are no further details in the article); openness to experiences; leadership experiences score from the seven leadership items.\n4. Create parcel indicators - each construct has more than five items so randomly combine items into three parcels per construct to serve as indicators of the latent variables.\n5. Use SEM to check if the parcels load onto their intended latent constructs and estimate the structural model where secure attachment predicts trait anxiety and openness to experiences, and trait anxiety and openness to experiences predict leadership experiences.\n7. Evaluate the relationship between openness to experience and leadership experiences.",
